If your business deals in food you must:

* make sure food is [safe to eat](http://www.food.gov.uk/foodindustry/regulation/hygleg/hyglegresources/sfbb/ "Safer food, better business"){:rel="external"}
* make sure you don’t add, remove or treat food in a way that makes it harmful to eat
* make sure the food is the same quality that you say it is
* make sure you don’t mislead people by the way food is labelled, advertised or marketed 
* keep records on where you got food from and show this information on demand - known as [‘traceability’ (PDF, 86KB)](http://www.food.gov.uk/multimedia/pdfs/fsa1782002guidance.pdf "Food Standards Agency"){:rel="external"}
* withdraw unsafe food and complete an incident report
* tell people why food has been withdrawn or recalled, eg a leaflet or poster

###Food additives

If you use an additive in food you must:

* only use an [approved additive](http://www.food.gov.uk/safereating/additivesbranch/enumberlist  "List of approved food additives"){:rel="external"}
* only use it if it is [approved for use in that food](http://ec.europa.eu/food/food/fAEF/additives/lists_authorised_fA_en.htm "Food additive maximum levels"){:rel="external"}
* the food additive doesn't exceed the [maximum permitted level (PDF, 170KB)](http://ec.europa.eu/food/food/fAEF/additives/lists_authorised_fA_en.htm "Food additive maximum levels"){:rel="external"} 

